# Lesson Plan Generator

This repository contains a Streamlit app that generates lesson plans based on recurring class schedules and specified holidays. You can input class details, select recurring days, and specify any dates to skip, and the app will generate a lesson plan accordingly.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.x installed on your machine
- Streamlit installed (`pip install streamlit`)

### Installation

1. Clone this repository to your local machine:

    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/yourusername/lesson-plan-generator.git
    ```

2. Navigate to the project directory:

    ```bash
    cd lesson-plan-generator
    ```

3. Install the required Python packages:

    ```bash
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    ```

### Running the App Locally

To run the app on your local machine:

1. Ensure you're in the root directory of the project.
2. Run the Streamlit app using the following command:

    ```bash
    streamlit run src/app.py
    ```

    Replace `src/app.py` with the correct path to your main Python file if it's different.

### Deploying the App on Streamlit Cloud

1. Go to [Streamlit Cloud](https://streamlit.io/cloud) and log in.
2. Select the option to deploy a new app.
3. Provide the GitHub repository URL: `https://github.com/yourusername/lesson-plan-generator`
4. Specify the main file path relative to the root of the repository. For example:

    ```
    src/app.py
    ```

    Adjust the file path according to the location of your main Python file.

### Customization

- You can modify the lesson plan logic in the main file (`src/app.py`) to suit different scheduling needs.
- Update the list of holidays or off-days dynamically by editing the respective parts in the code.

